  (text "Powder-doser actuator stack (issue #24).  Connectivity is\nexpressed by matching global net labels (KiCad treats identically\nnamed labels as the same net).  Pi GPIO labels (PI_GPIO16/18/20/21,\nI2C_SDA/SCL) name the Pi pin that the bonnet header passes through." (at 50 15 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top))
    (uuid 99f15e4f-71a8-4146-97ba-9d69b8a59ba7)
  )
  (text "DRV8825 microstep mode pins M0/M1/M2 are tied low here =>\nfull-step default.  Tie all three to +3V3 for 1/32 ustep.\nRST/SLP must be high for the driver to run.\nSet Vref pot to ~0.42 V (=> ~0.67 A/phase) before powering motor." (at 230 285 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top))
    (uuid ca00ff1f-f543-4f6b-aff8-00160639d08c)
  )
  (text "PLACEHOLDER SYMBOLS (no first-party Adafruit/Pololu KiCad lib exists):\n  - Adafruit DRV2605L (#2305), DRV8871 (#3190), Perma-Proto Bonnet\n    (#2310), and the Pololu DRV8825 carrier (#2133) are drawn as\n    labelled rectangles defined in powder_doser.kicad_sym.\n  - If the BYU PSC has any of these boards already in a local KiCad\n    library, swap the powder_doser:* refs for the real ones.\nASSUMED CONNECTIONS that need a human to confirm:\n  - JF-0530B solenoid coil polarity is irrelevant in tap mode.\n  - Stepper coil pairs A1/A2 and B1/B2 must match the chosen\n    NEMA-11 SKU's datasheet (varies by vendor).\n  - The 5 V and 12 V supplies share a common GND with the Pi.\n  - DRV8871 IN2 is tied to GND for one-direction PWM tap mode." (at 230 15 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top))
    (uuid 0fe0146e-f3db-48a1-a20b-721c1640d76e)
  )

  (sheet_instances
    (path "/" (page "1"))
  )
)
